notesStmt.note: This manuscript is an illuminated and illustrated copy of the collection of poems (dīvān) by Shams al-Dīn Muḥammad Ḥāfiz al-Shīrāzī (fl. eighth century AH / fourteenth CE). The text was written in nastaʿlīq script in black ink on buff and rose-tinted laid paper in Shawwāl 958 AH / 1552 CE. The codex contains four illustrations (fols. 41a, 95b, 147a, and 179b). The dark brown goatskin binding with central medallion and pendants panel-stamped in relief is original to the manuscript.

msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is Persian.

supportDesc.foliation: Foliation in Hindu-Arabic numerals beginning with the first double-page opening

layoutDesc.layout: Framing lines in gold, black, and blue

handDesc.handNote: Written in nastaʿlīq script in black ink

decoDesc.decoNote: Four illustrations (fols. 41a, 95b, 147a, and 179b); illuminated incipit with headpiece (fol. 1b); interlinear illumination (fols. 1b-2a)

decoNote.title: Illuminated incipit page with headpiece
decoNote.note: This page has an illuminated headpiece inscribed wa-Llah khayr hāfiz. The main text is decorated with interlinear illumination with polychrome motifs. The vertical divider is illuminated with floral motifs on a blue ground. The headpiece and written surface are surrounded by a dark blue band with white crosses and an illuminated frame.

decoNote.title: Youth and pir in a garden
